## API Reference

### POST /api/urls/ — Create Short URL

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/urls/ \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "original_url": "https://www.google.com",
    "custom_code": "goog",
    "expires_in_hours": 72
  }'
```

Response `201`:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "short_code": "goog",
    "short_url": "http://localhost:3000/goog",
    "original_url": "https://www.google.com",
    "clicks": 0,
    "expires_at": "2024-01-04T12:00:00Z",
    "created_at": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z"
  }
}
```

---

### GET /:code — Redirect

```bash
# Follow the redirect with -L
curl -L http://localhost:3000/goog

# Or open in browser:
# http://localhost:3000/goog
```

Returns `302 Found` → redirects to `https://www.google.com`

---

### GET /api/urls/:code — Get Stats

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/urls/goog
```

Response `200`:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "short_code": "goog",
    "short_url": "http://localhost:3000/goog",
    "original_url": "https://www.google.com",
    "clicks": 17,
    "created_at": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z"
  }
}
```

---

### GET /api/urls/ — List All URLs

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/api/urls/
```

Response `200`:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "count": 3,
  "data": [ ... ]
}
```

---

### DELETE /api/urls/:code — Delete URL

```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/urls/goog
```

Response `200`:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Short URL deleted successfully"
}
```

---

### GET /health — Health Check

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/health
```

Response `200`:
```json
{ "status": "ok", "service": "url-shortener" }
```

---

## Error Responses

All errors follow the same shape:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": "Short URL not found"
}
```

| Status | When |
|--------|------|
| 400    | Invalid URL or bad request body |
| 404    | Short code doesn't exist |
| 409    | Custom code already taken |
| 410    | Short URL has expired |
| 500    | Unexpected server error |

---

## Go Concepts Demonstrated

| Concept | File |
|---------|------|
| Structs & methods | models/url.go |
| Interfaces | URLRepository, URLService |
| Error wrapping (`%w`) | repository, service |
| Sentinel errors | `ErrNotFound`, `ErrURLExpired` |
| Goroutines | Click counter in service (fire-and-forget) |
| Pointer receivers | GORM model methods |
| Dependency injection | cmd/main.go |
| Variadic middleware | `app.Use(...)` in main.go |

---

## Fiber vs Gin — Key Differences in Code

### Context object
```go
// Gin
func (h *Handler) Create(c *gin.Context) {
    c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)
    c.JSON(201, gin.H{"data": resp})
}

// Fiber
func (h *Handler) Create(c *fiber.Ctx) error {   // returns error!
    c.BodyParser(&req)
    return c.Status(201).JSON(fiber.Map{"data": resp})
}
```

### Key difference
Fiber handlers return `error` — this lets Fiber's error handler
centralise all error responses. Gin handlers return nothing.

### Route params
```go
c.Param("code")    // Gin
c.Params("code")   // Fiber
```

### JSON response
```go
c.JSON(200, gin.H{"key": "value"})      // Gin
c.Status(200).JSON(fiber.Map{"key": "value"}) // Fiber
```